&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Magnolia, the Safety &amp;amp; Workers’ Compensation Specialist supports workplace safety and workers’ compensation programs by managing incident reporting, claim administration, OSHA compliance, and safety training initiatives. This position collaborates with operational leaders to reduce risk, support injured employees, and promote a safe work environment. The Safety &amp;amp; Workers’ Compensation Specialist manages day‑to‑day safety and workers’ compensation operations while maintaining accurate documentation and compliance. This position works from Magnolia Headquarters in Waco, Texas. It reports to the Employee Relations and Risk Compliance Manager and has no supervisory responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct workplace safety programs, inspections, audits, and hazard assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate or deliver required safety training, maintaining accurate training records for completion, expiration, recertification as needed*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with OSHA, state safety laws, and organizational standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and implement safety policies and procedures in compliance with local, state, and federal law including Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) and Department of Transportation (DOT) regulations*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain SDS (Safety Data Sheet) library, signage, safety equipment, and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain OSHA logs (300, 301, 300A) and ensure timely reporting and postings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and coordinate safety training, communications, policies, procedures and programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and ensure compliance with hazardous communication standards and hazardous materials disposal procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as first point of contact for workplace injury reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate and manage workers’ compensation claims&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in safety and workers compensation incident investigations to determine root causes and corrective actions*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and communicate in a timely manner with worker’s compensation carriers, medical providers, and employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track claim progress, return‑to‑work status, and restricted duty arrangements for workers’ compensation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain worker’s compensation files, incident investigations, and safety records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze injury and claim trends and recommend preventive actions, proactive actions, and cost containment measures*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate and coordinate safety committees, ergonomics initiatives, and risk reduction projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designate safety committee members across the organization and conduct ongoing committee meetings*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with HR, Facilities, Operations, and Legal on safety and injury management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Metrics evaluated on Performance Review&lt;/p&gt;
